# Release SOC Compliance Tracker – Phase 6
# Release Readiness Dashboard, Background Job Processing & Performance Optimization

## Objective

This phase focuses on improving the overall user experience and backend performance of the Release Readiness module.

The current implementation is functionally correct, but the Release Readiness page has become very lengthy, and the Generate Report process blocks the user until every downstream task completes. The objective is to redesign the user experience, execute long-running tasks asynchronously, significantly improve backend performance, and provide better visibility into job execution.

Before implementation:

- Analyze the existing project structure.
- Reuse existing services, repositories, DTOs, controllers and React components.
- Do not duplicate business logic.
- Follow the current project architecture and coding standards.
- Keep the implementation modular, maintainable and production-ready.

