# 12. Performance Optimization

Review the complete backend implementation.

Identify slow operations.

Optimize wherever possible.

Focus especially on:

- GitHub API calls
- Branch retrieval
- Kubernetes API calls
- Database access
- External integrations

---

# 13. Reactive Programming

The current implementation appears to process many external calls sequentially.

Replace sequential processing wherever appropriate with reactive parallel execution.

Preferred technology:

Spring WebFlux

Use:

- Flux
- Mono

Run independent external API calls in parallel.

Examples include:

- GitHub branch retrieval
- Repository metadata
- Kubernetes deployments
- ConfigMap retrieval
- SAST lookups

Avoid unnecessary for-loops that perform blocking network calls.

Use bounded parallelism to avoid overwhelming external systems.

---

# 14. Database Optimization

Review database access.

Improve:

- SQL queries
- Index usage
- Batch inserts
- Batch updates
- Pagination where applicable
- Connection reuse

Reduce unnecessary database round-trips.

---

# 15. API Optimization

Review REST APIs.

Reduce:

- Duplicate calls
- Duplicate DTO mapping
- Redundant serialization
- Repeated repository access

Implement caching where appropriate.

---

# 16. UI Performance

Reduce unnecessary React re-renders.

Lazy load heavy sections.

Load only the selected Release Readiness section.

Avoid loading all tables simultaneously.

---

# 17. Dashboard Loading

Dashboard summary cards should load first.

Detailed tables should only load when the user selects the corresponding section.

This should significantly improve perceived performance.

